				caption: '',
				content: "‘His being’; the word we find in the Greek here is hypostasis, which the Latins translated by ‘substance’, while the Greek theologians used it to mean ‘person’."
			},
					3363: {
				id_comment: 3363,
				source_str: '✻',
				caption: '',
				content: "The contrast here instituted between the Divine Word and the holy Angels may have some reference to contemporary errors (cf. Col. 2.18); but its immediate purpose is to lead up to the beginning of ch. 2, where the new Covenant instituted by Jesus Christ is contrasted with the old Covenant, revealed by angels on mount Sinai (Ac. 7.53, Gal. 3.19)."
			},
					3364: {
				id_comment: 3364,
				source_str: '✻',
